---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import BrandBranchesGrid from '../../components/BrandBranchesGrid.astro';
import { MAIN_PHONE, MAIN_PHONE_TEL } from '../../data/branches';

const title = "Haier Refrigerator Repair | Southern California | Apartment + Compact";
const description = "Haier refrigerator repair across Southern California — compact top-freezer, French-door, side-by-side, wine + beverage. Chinese parent of GE Appliances since 2016. $89 diagnostic. (424) 325-0520.";
const canonical = "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/haier-refrigerator-repair/";

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "Is Haier actually Chinese — and is that why GE fridges are branded Haier sometimes?",
    a: "Yes and yes, with a nuance worth understanding. Haier Group is the Chinese home-appliance parent headquartered in Qingdao, founded in 1984. In June 2016 Haier acquired GE Appliances from General Electric for $5.6 billion — GE Appliances continues to operate independently from its Louisville, Kentucky headquarters, and GE, GE Profile, GE Café, and GE Monogram are still marketed and manufactured as GE-branded products under the long-term brand license. The Haier-branded product line sold in the US is a separate lineup focused on compact, apartment, small-space, and second-fridge configurations — 24-inch counter-depth top-freezers, compact French-doors, wine and beverage centers, mini-fridges. When you see \"Haier refrigerator\" in a big-box store or on Home Depot's site, it's this compact-focused line — not the full-size premium GE lineup. The parent-brand engineering shares platforms and parts across Haier Group's US operations, which is why our techs keep both Haier-branded and GE-branded parts in dispatch rotation."
  },
  {
    q: "Is Haier the same as GE Appliances — should I just call GE for service?",
    a: "They're in the same corporate family but they're different product lines with different warranty paths. GE Appliances and Haier are sibling brands under Haier Group's US operation (Haier also owns Fisher & Paykel + DCS since 2012). For warranty service, the brand badge on the product dictates the service path: Haier-branded unit goes through Haier customer service; GE-branded unit goes through GE customer service. Out of warranty — which is when most of our Haier service calls happen — the brand-family context actually helps. Haier and GE share manufacturing platforms for certain compressors, fans, ice-maker modules, and control boards; our techs routinely source parts from the broader Haier Group parts catalog when the Haier-branded part is on backorder and a compatible GE-family part exists. That's a real advantage for LA households — Haier's US parts network is meaningfully more developed since the GE acquisition than it was pre-2016."
  },
  {
    q: "What kinds of Haier refrigerators are common in LA — we keep seeing small ones in apartments?",
    a: "Haier's LA installed base skews heavily toward compact and small-space configurations because that's the brand's US positioning. The most common Haier refrigerators our techs see: the 24-inch counter-depth top-freezer (HA10TG21 series, 9.8 cu ft, showing up in Koreatown, Hollywood, Westwood, and DTLA apartments); compact French-door models under 30 inches (guesthouses, pool houses, ADUs in West LA and the Valley); wine and beverage centers (Sherman Oaks and Encino home-bar installs); mini-fridges (dorm, office, home-gym). Full-size Haier French-door and side-by-side models exist but aren't the brand's volume lineup in the US — households buying full-size premium typically land on GE, GE Profile, or sibling mainstream brands instead. This matters for service because compact and ADU-mounted fridges have different failure patterns than full-size kitchen flagships — defrost drain tube freeze-ups (compact layout routes tighter than full-size), door-gasket compression on frequently-opened second fridges, and ice-maker module failures on the smaller ice-maker platforms used in compact units."
  },
  {
    q: "Our Haier compact fridge isn't cooling — what's the usual cause?",
    a: "Warm compartment on a compact Haier, in order of likelihood: (1) condenser coil dust or blocked rear clearance — compacts installed in cabinetry or tight ADU layouts often run with less rear clearance than full-size fridges need, reducing heat rejection; (2) evaporator fan bearing wear — the single-fan architecture common on compact Haier puts all airflow through one motor, so bearing wear shows up as humming plus warm-compartment symptoms; (3) defrost drain tube freeze-up — if the drain tube clogs with ice, defrost meltwater can't escape, builds up, and freezes the evaporator; eventually the whole refrigeration cycle fails; (4) start/run capacitor on the compressor — less common on newer Haier units (post-2018 generations have upgraded electronics), common on pre-2015 Haier compact fridges still in service. Diagnostic ranges: condenser clean $160–$240; evaporator fan $220–$380; defrost drain clear + heater check $220–$360; capacitor $180–$260."
  },
  {
    q: "We bought a Haier top-freezer for an ADU — parts are tough to find online. Can you service it?",
    a: "Yes. Haier's 24-inch counter-depth top-freezer platform (HA10TG21 family and predecessors) is one of the most-installed Haier configurations in LA's ADU + guesthouse + pool-house + rental-studio segment, and our parts channel handles it directly. Parts availability has improved meaningfully since Haier's 2016 GE acquisition consolidated the US distribution — we source through the Haier Appliances channel in Louisville. Typical part lead times: control board 3–7 days, thermostat / cold-control 2–4 days, door gasket (size-specific profile) 5–10 days, compressor (post-warranty replacement) 7–14 days. For older Haier units (pre-2016 pre-acquisition inventory), some parts are discontinued — we substitute with compatible Whirlpool or Frigidaire platform equivalents where the mounting and electrical specs match, and advise honestly when a repair isn't economical relative to unit replacement cost on these budget-tier compact fridges."
  },
  {
    q: "Haier ice maker not working — is it worth fixing or should we just not use it?",
    a: "Honest field read: depends on which Haier line and the unit's age. On the compact top-freezer platform, the ice-maker module is a cost-effective swap ($280–$420 module + install) when the host unit is under ~6 years old and otherwise sound. On older compact Haier units (pre-2018), the ice maker's modular architecture is reliable enough that repair makes sense. On larger Haier French-door units the ice-maker assemblies are more complex (dual-ice, dispenser-integrated, filter-dependent) and the repair economics shift — module $380–$580, plus potential water-inlet valve and filter-housing service. For compact Haier in second-fridge applications (guesthouses, ADUs, home bars), our techs sometimes advise clients that using a standalone countertop ice maker is cheaper than fixing an integrated ice maker on a $900-new-unit-price-range compact refrigerator. For primary-kitchen Haier or French-door models, integrated ice-maker repair is usually the right call."
  },
  {
    q: "Haier French-door refrigerator — less common in LA, but we have one. Service any different?",
    a: "Yes, partly different from the compact top-freezer platform. Haier's full-size French-door lineup in the US has grown since the GE acquisition — larger capacity (22–27 cu ft), counter-depth and standard-depth options, in-door ice + water dispensers on higher trims. Service profile overlaps with GE-family French-door platforms more than with compact Haier: dual-evaporator architecture on some models (separate fridge + freezer evap coils), more sophisticated electronic control, ice-and-water door-dispenser service items. Common service on full-size Haier French-door: ice-maker module ($380–$580), evaporator fan (specific to the freezer-section or fridge-section fan based on which compartment is warm), in-door water dispenser valve, LED lighting module failures on earlier generations. Repair costs run closer to GE mainstream pricing than to compact-Haier budget pricing."
  },
  {
    q: "Does Haier parts support work for older pre-2016 Haier refrigerators still in service?",
    a: "Partially — and this is one of the real repair-vs-replace decision points for older Haier units. Pre-2016 Haier refrigerators (before the GE acquisition consolidated Haier's US distribution) had a thinner parts network and some of those early-2010s parts are now discontinued or require long-lead international sourcing. Our diagnostic approach on pre-2016 Haier: identify the specific part needed, check Haier Appliances availability, check compatible Whirlpool or Frigidaire platform substitutes for basic items (fans, thermostats, capacitors), and advise candidly on repair economics. On pre-2016 Haier units 10-plus years old, replacement rather than major refrigeration-cycle repair is often the economic answer — particularly since Haier's current compact line is priced so that a repair approaching $500–$700 may equal half the replacement cost of a new comparable unit. For post-2016 Haier (acquisition-era onward), parts support is substantially better and repairs are generally worthwhile."
  },
  {
    q: "Haier is the parent of Fisher & Paykel and DCS — but my fridge is badged Haier, not F&P. Are the parts interchangeable?",
    a: "Only partially, and the \"interchangeable\" label overpromises. Haier Group's US portfolio includes three distinct brand ecosystems: Haier (budget/compact/apartment), GE Appliances (mainstream full-size, with GE/Profile/Café/Monogram tiers), and Fisher & Paykel + DCS (premium full-size, including integrated and outdoor). Platform sharing exists at the compressor, fan motor, and some control-board level where Haier's global engineering has consolidated components, but the finished-good assembly specs (mounting, electrical harnesses, door-configuration hardware) are brand-specific. Our techs don't swap F&P parts into Haier-branded fridges as default practice — the part numbers and specifications differ even where the underlying function is similar. Where cross-brand substitution makes sense (e.g., a specific capacitor spec shared across platforms, a fan-motor part number common to multiple Haier Group SKUs), we apply it with verification. See <a href='/brands/fisher-paykel-refrigerator-repair/'>Fisher & Paykel refrigerator repair</a> for the F&P-specific service profile."
  },
  {
    q: "What does Haier refrigerator repair cost in LA?",
    a: "Residential diagnostic is $89, waived when you authorize the repair. Common Haier bands: condenser coil clean + diagnostic $160–$240; door gasket replacement $180–$320 (compact), $220–$360 (full-size French-door); thermostat / cold-control $200–$340; compressor start/run capacitor $180–$260; evaporator fan motor $220–$380 (compact), $260–$440 (full-size); defrost drain clear + heater test $220–$360; condenser fan motor $240–$400; ice-maker module $280–$420 (compact), $380–$580 (full-size French-door); main control board $340–$560; water-inlet valve (full-size with dispenser) $240–$380; compressor replacement (post-warranty) $800–$1,400. On compact Haier units under $1,000 replacement cost, we discuss repair economics honestly — some repairs approach half the replacement cost of a new unit, and we'd rather have that conversation than push a repair that doesn't pencil out."
  }
];

const schemaJsons = [
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "LocalBusiness",
    "@id": canonical + "#business",
    "name": "Same Day Appliance Repair — Haier Refrigerator Service",
    "image": "https://samedayappliance.repair/images/same-day-appliance-repair.png",
    "url": canonical,
    "telephone": MAIN_PHONE_TEL,
    "priceRange": "$$",
    "areaServed": [
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Los Angeles County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Orange County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Ventura County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "San Bernardino County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Riverside County" }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Service",
    "serviceType": "Haier Refrigerator Repair",
    "provider": { "@id": canonical + "#business" },
    "areaServed": [
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Los Angeles County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Orange County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Ventura County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "San Bernardino County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Riverside County" }
    ],
    "description": "Haier refrigerator repair across Los Angeles — compact 24-inch counter-depth top-freezer, French-door, side-by-side, wine + beverage centers, mini-fridges. Haier Group (China, 1984) parent of GE Appliances since 2016 and Fisher & Paykel + DCS since 2012. Apartment, ADU, guesthouse, and second-fridge service focus. $89 residential diagnostic waived with repair.",
    "offers": {
      "@type": "Offer",
      "priceSpecification": {
        "@type": "PriceSpecification",
        "price": "89.00",
        "priceCurrency": "USD",
        "description": "Residential diagnostic fee, waived with repair"
      }
    }
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": faqs.map(f => ({
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": f.q,
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": f.a }
    }))
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
    "itemListElement": [
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Brands", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Haier", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/haier/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 4, "name": "Haier Refrigerator Repair", "item": canonical }
    ]
  }
];
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} canonical={canonical}>
  <Fragment slot="head-scripts">
    {schemaJsons.map((schema) => (
      <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(schema)} />
    ))}
  </Fragment>

  <div class="call-banner">
    <div class="wrap">
      <span>Haier fridge not cooling? Same-day service across LA:</span>
      <a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="phone-lg">{MAIN_PHONE}</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="hero"><div class="wrap">
          <div class="crumb"><a href="/">Home</a> › <a href="/brands/">Brands</a> › Haier › Refrigerator Repair</div>
          <h1>Haier Refrigerator Repair</h1>
          <p class="lede">
            Haier is the Qingdao, China-based home-appliance manufacturer founded in 1984 and the parent company
            of GE Appliances (since 2016) and Fisher &amp; Paykel + DCS (since 2012). The Haier-branded US product
            line is a separate lineup focused on compact 24-inch counter-depth top-freezers, smaller French-door
            and side-by-side configurations, wine and beverage centers, and mini-fridges — the second-fridge,
            apartment, ADU, and guesthouse segment. Our techs service Haier across LA's apartment-heavy
            neighborhoods (Koreatown, Hollywood, Westwood, DTLA, Mid-Wilshire) and across West LA and Valley
            properties where ADUs, pool houses, and guesthouses drive compact-fridge installs. Same-day dispatch,
            $89 residential diagnostic waived with the repair.
          </p>
          <div class="hero-cta">
            <a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="btn btn-primary">Call {MAIN_PHONE}</a>
            <a href="#book" class="btn btn-ghost">Request a Visit</a>
          </div>
          <ul class="hero-facts">
            <li><b>Haier Group China since 1984</b> — parent of GE Appliances (2016) + F&amp;P / DCS (2012)</li>
            <li><b>Compact + apartment focus</b> — 24" counter-depth top-freezer is the LA volume platform</li>
            <li><b>Parts network improved post-2016</b> — GE-acquisition consolidation via Louisville distribution</li>
            <li><b>$89 residential diagnostic</b> — waived when you authorize the repair</li>
          </ul>
        </div></section>

  <BrandBranchesGrid />

  <section class="trust-bar">
    <div class="wrap">
      <span>CSLB #1138898 · Insured</span>
      <span>Same-day in 5 SoCal counties</span>
      <span>Residential diagnostic $89 · waived with repair</span>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap narrow">
      <h2>Haier in LA — compact-fridge volume brand with a big corporate parent</h2>
      <p>
        Haier's US positioning is different from most refrigerator brands we service. The Haier-branded product
        line sold through big-box retailers — Home Depot, Lowe's, Best Buy, Costco — focuses on compact 24-inch
        counter-depth top-freezers, smaller French-door and side-by-side configurations, wine and beverage
        centers, and mini-fridges. That's the apartment, ADU, guesthouse, dorm, office, and second-fridge
        segment. Meanwhile the Haier Group corporate umbrella is one of the largest home-appliance
        manufacturers in the world, with ownership of GE Appliances (acquired from General Electric for $5.6
        billion in June 2016 and still operated independently from Louisville, Kentucky) and Fisher &amp; Paykel
        + DCS (acquired 2012). So the service territory we see is: compact Haier-branded fridges in apartment
        and ADU installs, plus the full-size premium GE / Café / Monogram and F&amp;P / DCS product families
        under the same corporate parent but with distinct service paths.
      </p>
      <p>
        For LA specifically, Haier's installed base concentrates in apartment-heavy neighborhoods (Koreatown,
        Hollywood, Westwood, Downtown LA, Mid-Wilshire, East Hollywood), ADU and guesthouse installs across the
        Westside and Valley (Encino, Sherman Oaks, Studio City, Woodland Hills, Tarzana), and second-fridge or
        pool-house applications in luxury households where a compact unit serves the outdoor-entertainment area
        or a home bar. This geography matters for service — compact fridges installed in tight cabinetry, ADU
        kitchens with constrained ventilation clearance, and frequently-opened second-fridge applications
        develop failure patterns that differ from full-size primary-kitchen refrigerators. Our techs calibrate
        accordingly: condenser clearance assessment first, defrost-cycle integrity second, door-gasket check
        third on frequently-opened compacts.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section alt">
    <div class="wrap">
      <h2>Haier refrigerator failures our techs see most often</h2>
      <p class="intro">
        Pattern data from our Haier coverage in LA. Compact Haier and full-size Haier have overlapping but
        distinct failure profiles — worth separating in the diagnostic.
      </p>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>Warm compartment on compact top-freezer — condenser clearance + dust</h3>
        <p>
          Most common Haier service call on the 24-inch counter-depth top-freezer platform. Symptom: fridge
          compartment gradually runs warm, especially in summer, particularly when the unit is installed in
          tight cabinetry or an ADU nook with limited rear ventilation clearance. Diagnostic order: verify
          rear clearance meets the Haier install spec (typically 1–2 inches), clean condenser coil dust
          buildup, verify condenser fan operation. Condenser clean + clearance advisory $160–$240.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>Defrost drain freeze-up on compact Haier</h3>
        <p>
          Compact refrigerators have tighter internal plumbing than full-size fridges — the defrost drain
          tube routes through a more constrained path, and when it clogs with ice, defrost meltwater backs
          up, freezes around the evaporator, and eventually interrupts the entire refrigeration cycle. Symptom
          progression: standing water in the bottom freezer tray, then ice buildup visible on back wall, then
          cooling failure. Fix is drain clear + defrost heater + thermostat verification. $220–$360.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>Evaporator fan bearing wear — single-fan compact architecture</h3>
        <p>
          Haier compact fridges use single-evaporator-fan architecture (one fan moves air across both the
          freezer and fridge compartments through shared ducting). When the fan bearing wears, airflow
          degrades across both compartments simultaneously, and the humming or rattling noise signature
          becomes characteristic. Fan replacement $220–$380. More common after 6–8 years of continuous
          operation in second-fridge applications where the unit runs essentially 24/7.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>Ice-maker module failures on compact + French-door</h3>
        <p>
          Haier compact ice-maker modules (common on the counter-depth top-freezer with factory ice option)
          and Haier French-door ice-maker modules (dual-ice and in-door variants) both show module failures
          at 5–8 years. Compact module swap $280–$420; full-size French-door module $380–$580. Sometimes
          accompanied by water-inlet valve service or filter-housing cleaning.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>Door gasket compression loss on frequently-opened second fridges</h3>
        <p>
          Pool-house and outdoor-entertaining compact Haier fridges get opened constantly during summer — the
          door gaskets compress faster than primary-kitchen refrigerators and lose seal quality at 5–7 years
          rather than the 8–10 year profile on low-frequency main fridges. Gasket replacement $180–$320 on
          compact platforms.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>Main control board on post-2016 Haier electronic-control units</h3>
        <p>
          Newer Haier refrigerators (post-GE-acquisition era) have electronic control boards that occasionally
          fail from capacitor aging or humidity damage in ADU or pool-house installs with marginal moisture
          control. Board swap $340–$560. Earlier pre-2016 Haier units with simpler electro-mechanical controls
          are typically repaired via cold-control replacement instead.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap">
      <h2>Haier US refrigerator product lines we service</h2>
      <p class="intro">
        Haier's US-branded lineup emphasizes compact and second-fridge configurations. Full-size Haier French-
        door and side-by-side models exist but aren't the volume platform. Our service coverage spans all
        current Haier-branded configurations.
      </p>
      <div class="model-grid">
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>24" counter-depth top-freezer (HA10TG21 family)</h3>
          <p>The LA Haier volume platform. 9.8 cubic feet, 24-inch width, counter-depth profile suited to
          apartment kitchens, ADU builds, pool houses, and second-fridge installs. Available in white,
          stainless, and black finishes. Spill-proof glass shelves, humidity-controlled crisper, LED interior
          lighting. ADA compliant. Most common Haier refrigerator our techs service.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>Full-size French-door refrigerator</h3>
          <p>Larger-capacity Haier French-door models (22–27 cu ft) in counter-depth and standard-depth
          configurations. In-door ice + water dispenser options on higher trims. Dual-evaporator architecture
          on some models. Service profile overlaps more with GE-family French-door than with compact Haier.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>Side-by-side refrigerator</h3>
          <p>Standard 33–36" side-by-side configurations with ice + water through-the-door dispenser. Less
          common in LA than Haier's compact lineup but present in rental-property and mid-market kitchen
          refreshes. Service items include water-inlet valve, dispenser assembly, ice maker, evaporator fan.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>Wine and beverage centers</h3>
          <p>Undercounter and freestanding wine storage, beverage coolers, dual-zone units. Home-bar installs
          in Sherman Oaks, Encino, Hollywood Hills. Service: thermoelectric or compressor-cooling module
          depending on model, door-seal service, interior LED.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>Mini-fridges + compact apartment refrigerators</h3>
          <p>Dorm-style and apartment-compact mini-fridges under 5 cu ft. Home gym, office, ADU, guest bedroom.
          Repair economics can be marginal at this price point — we advise honestly when replacement is more
          economical than repair on small-volume units.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>Bottom-freezer + specialty configurations</h3>
          <p>Bottom-freezer Haier and specialty configurations including beer dispensers and outdoor-rated
          units. Lower volume across our service area. Parts and service handled through the same Haier Appliances channel
          as the mainstream Haier-branded lineup.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section alt">
    <div class="wrap narrow">
      <h2>Haier vs GE / Profile / Café / Monogram — the Haier Group brand disambiguation</h2>
      <p>
        Haier Group's US refrigerator portfolio runs across four distinct brand positions. Getting the brand
        right matters for parts sourcing, service path, and warranty handling.
      </p>
      <p>
        <b>Haier (compact / apartment / budget)</b> — the Haier-branded US line. Compact top-freezer,
        apartment, ADU, second-fridge, mini, wine and beverage. This is the page you're reading.
      </p>
      <p>
        <b>GE (mainstream)</b> — GE Appliances' mainstream full-size line. Standard French-door, side-by-side,
        top-freezer, bottom-freezer. Biggest installed base in mainstream LA households. See
        <a href="/brands/ge-refrigerator-repair/">GE refrigerator repair</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        <b>GE Profile (feature-focused premium)</b> — above mainstream GE; Full-Width Freezer Drawer,
        SmartHQ Wi-Fi, advanced French-door features. See
        <a href="/brands/ge-profile-refrigerator-repair/">GE Profile refrigerator repair</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        <b>GE Café (style-first premium)</b> — customizable brass / matte black / matte white handles,
        Keurig K-Cup integrated fridge models, style-forward design. See
        <a href="/brands/ge-cafe-refrigerator-repair/">GE Café refrigerator repair</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        <b>GE Monogram (ultra-luxury)</b> — column built-in, Statement and Minimalist collections, $5K–$25K
        appliance range. See <a href="/brands/ge-monogram-refrigerator-repair/">GE Monogram refrigerator
        repair</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        <b>Fisher &amp; Paykel + DCS (premium full-size, also Haier Group)</b> — separate acquisition (2012),
        premium positioning, integrated and outdoor. See
        <a href="/brands/fisher-paykel-refrigerator-repair/">F&amp;P refrigerator repair</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        The short version: Haier-branded = compact and budget. GE-branded (and its premium tiers) = full-size
        mainstream through luxury. F&amp;P / DCS-branded = premium and integrated. All under Haier Group
        corporate parent, all serviced by our team — but with distinct parts channels and service approaches.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap">
      <h2>What Haier refrigerator repair typically costs</h2>
      <p class="intro">Haier compact-platform pricing runs below mainstream US brands on labor-light service;
      parts lead times improved meaningfully after the 2016 GE acquisition consolidated Haier's Louisville
      distribution. Residential diagnostic $89, waived with repair.</p>
      <table class="price-table">
        <tr><th>Service</th><th>Typical Range</th><th>Notes</th></tr>
        <tr><td>Residential diagnostic</td><td>$89</td><td>Flat, waived if repair is authorized same visit</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Condenser coil clean + clearance check</td><td>$160 – $240</td><td>Primary compact-fridge service</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Door gasket replacement (compact)</td><td>$180 – $320</td><td>24" and 30" profile</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Door gasket replacement (full-size French-door)</td><td>$220 – $360</td><td>Two-door profile</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Thermostat / cold-control replacement</td><td>$200 – $340</td><td>Electro-mechanical on older units</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Compressor start / run capacitor</td><td>$180 – $260</td><td>8–12 year common service</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Evaporator fan motor (compact)</td><td>$220 – $380</td><td>Single-fan architecture</td></tr>
